SIMPLE: uranus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uranus
<hw>U"ra*nus</hw> <pr>(-n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Uranus</ets>, Gr. <grk>O'yrano`s</grk> Uranus, <grk>o'yrano`s</grk>
heaven, sky. Cf. <er>Uranium</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld> <def>The son or husband of Gaia
(Earth), and father of Chronos (Time) and the Titans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>One of the primary planets. It
is about 1,800,000,000 miles from the sun, about 36,000 miles in
diameter, and its period of revolution round the sun is nearly 84 of our
years.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This planet has also been called
<altname>Herschel</altname>, from Sir William Herschel, who discovered
it in 1781, and who named it <altname>Georgium Sidus</altname>, in honor
of George III., then King of England.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uran-utan</ent>⟦br⟧
